Over%20the%20decades%2C%20technology%20and%20funding%20challenges%20have%20hampered%20the%20nation's%20hopes%20of%20crewed%20flights.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20NASA%20announced%20it%20was%20funding%20a%20revolutionary%20high-thrust%20rocket%20%E2%80%94%20called%20a%20Pulsed%20Plasma%20Rocket%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20make%20crewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-mars-martian-habitat-icon-3d-printed-space-texas-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emissions%20to%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20just%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20seven%20months%20faster%20than%20it'd%20take%20with%20current%20technology%20and%20would%20drastically%20reduce%20the%20risk%20and%20cost%20of%20a%20crewed%20Mars%20mission%2C%20according%20to%20Howe%20Industries%2C%20which%20is%20developing%20the%20concept.%20It%20%26quot%3Bholds%20the%20potential%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-travel-space-tourist-visit-epic-tour-epic-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevolutionize%20space%20exploration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PPR%20is%20just%20one%20of%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20the%20US's%20decades-long%20discussion%20to%20send%20humans%20to%20Mars.%20In%20the%20early%20'60s%2C%20for%20example%2C%20nuclear-bomb-powered%20spaceships%20were%20proposed%20for%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20well%20before%20NASA%20landed%20the%20first%20humans%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20the%20US%20has%20poured%20money%20and%20time%20into%20proposals%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-mars-trip-cramped-difficult-hard-work-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrewed%20Mars%20mission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20to%20see%20its%20attempts%20never%20leave%20the%20ground.%20But%20technology%20isn't%20the%20only%20thing%20standing%20in%20the%20way.%20Politics%20also%20plays%20a%20big%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20kind%20of%20like%20a%20joke%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-nasa-has-not-sent-humans-to-mars-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espace%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20Mars%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Shindell%2C%20a%20curator%20with%20the%20National%20Air%20and%20Space%20Museum%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BPutting%20humans%20on%20Mars%20is%20always%2020%20years%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20short%20enough%20to%20seem%20tangible%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20long%20enough%20that%20the%20political%20situation%20will%20change%20before%20it%20can%20be%20realized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20fully%20understand%20why%20the%20US%20hasn't%20sent%20humans%20to%20Mars%2C%20despite%20sending%20more%20robots%20there%20than%20any%20other%20country%2C%20it%20just%20takes%20a%20trip%20down%20memory%20lane.%20Here's%20a%20history%20of%20the%20US's%20most%20promising%20crewed%20Martian%20missions%20that%20never%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1950s%3A%20The%20Mars%20Project%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wernher%20von%20Braun%20at%20his%20desk%20with%20moon%20lander%20in%20background%20and%20rocket%20models%20on%20his%20desk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644f8637415a05fdd089759%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWernher%20von%20Braun%20helped%20shape%20NASA's%20space%20program%20and%20was%20director%20of%20Marshall%20Space%20Flight%20Center.%3Cp%3EMarshall%20Space%20Flight%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20'40s%20and%20'50s%2C%20no%20one%20really%20knew%20what%20they%20might%20find%20on%20Mars%2C%20but%20they%20knew%20getting%20there%20would%20be%20tricky.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20to%20seriously%20tackle%20the%20problem%20was%20Wernher%20von%20Braun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20WWII%2C%20von%20Braun%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Nazi%20party%20and%20created%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnazi-v2-rocket-couldnt-stop-allies-but-influence-future-missiles-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EV-2%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20the%20war%2C%20he%20continued%20his%20work%20on%20missiles%20with%20the%20US%20Army%20as%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnazi-scientists-space-program-2014-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOperation%20Paperclip%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20also%20working%20on%20a%20novel%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Mars%20Project.%26quot%3B%20In%20it%2C%20he%20laid%20out%20the%20first%20detailed%20plan%20to%20send%20humans%20to%20the%20Red%20Planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20envisioned%20a%20260-day%20mission%20that%20would%20launch%20in%201985%20with%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E10%20spaceships%20and%2070%20crew%20members.%20%26quot%3BHe%20sat%20down%20and%20did%20the%20math%20and%20created%20a%20whole%20story%20around%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Shindell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%20'50s%2C%20von%20Braun%20consulted%20on%20NASA's%20very%20first%2010-year%20plan%2C%20which%20included%20sending%20the%20first%20probes%20to%20Mars.%20(Sending%20humans%20to%20Mars%20would%20come%20later.)%20What%20started%20as%20fiction%20got%20closer%20to%20reality%20when%20von%20Braun%20started%20working%20at%20NASA%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1960s%3A%20Mars%20by%201965%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20concept%20drawing%20of%20Project%20Orion%20with%20a%20nuclear-powered%20spaceshift%20labeled%20USA%20heading%20toward%20a%20planet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644f7a19fc063e829b15d44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20concept%20drawing%20for%20Project%20Orion%20shows%20a%20spacecraft%20powered%20by%20nuclear%20fission.%3Cp%3EMarshall%20Space%20Flight%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201950s%2C%20Theodore%20Taylor%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20nuclear%20weapons%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-at-los-alamos-during-manhattan-project-oppenheimer-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Alamos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20theoretical%20physicist%20Freeman%20Dyson%20embarked%20on%20an%20ambitious%20plan%20to%20build%20a%20nuclear-explosion-powered%20spaceship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalled%20Project%20Orion%2C%20the%20resulting%20ship%20would%20take%2012%20years%20to%20develop%2C%20cost%20%24100%20million%20per%20year%2C%20and%20comfortably%20hold%20150%20people.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETheir%20motto%20was%20%26quot%3BMars%20by%201965%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumans-astronauts-space-travel-saturn-possibility-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESaturn%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%201970.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHowever%2C%20NASA%20was%20concerned%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20any%20of%20the%20hundreds%20of%20bombs%20required%20to%20fuel%20the%20rocket%20exploded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201963%2C%20the%20team%20was%20having%20trouble%20getting%20increased%20funding.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20the%20nuclear%20test-ban%20treaty%20was%20signed%2C%20hampering%20the%20team's%20ability%20to%20test%20its%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20was%20canceled%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1965%3A%20Mars's%20first%20close-up%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221209%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-white%20image%20of%20Mars%20that%20was%20shown%20on%20TV%20in%201965%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644f6e914fb5b23cc5cbb41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20enhanced%20version%20of%20the%20first%20Mars%20photograph%20shown%20on%20TV%20in%201965.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FJPL-Caltech%2FDan%20Goods%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20NASA%20was%20feverishly%20working%20toward%20the%20moon%20in%20the%20'60s%2C%20it%20didn't%20fully%20abandon%20its%20plans%20for%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201962%2C%20German%20rocket%20scientist%20Ernst%20Stuhlinger%20was%20working%20at%20NASA%20on%20a%20project%20to%20get%20five%20crewed%20ships%20to%20the%20Red%20Planet%20by%20the%20early%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStuhlinger's%20planned%20ships%20were%20huge%2C%20almost%20500%20feet%20long.%20For%20comparison%2C%20NASA's%20Space%20Shuttles%20are%20under%20200%20feet.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20as%20NASA%20raced%20to%20land%20the%20first%20humans%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20it%20shifted%20focus%20to%20smaller%2C%20lighter%20spacecraft.%20This%20helped%20speed%20things%20along%20toward%20the%20moon%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20step%20back%20for%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pivot%20%26quot%3Breduced%20Apollo's%20utility%20as%20a%20technological%20stepping%20stone%20to%20Mars%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20S.%20F.%20Portree%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BHumans%20to%20Mars%3A%20Fifty%20Years%20of%20Mission%20Planning%2C%201950%E2%80%932000.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20NASA%20knew%20it%20needed%20more%20information%20about%20Mars%20before%20it%20landed%20humans%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethere.%20So%20in%201964%2C%20NASA's%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20launched%20the%20very%20first%20probe%20to%20fly%20by%20Mars%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-jpl-scientists-pieced-together-first-mars-image-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMariner%204%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20the%20probe%20transmitted%20to%20Earth%20were%20fuzzy%20and%20showed%20a%20desolate%2C%20barren%20planet.%20But%20they%20were%20the%20first%20close-up%20images%20of%20Mars's%20surface%20that%20anyone%20on%20Earth%20had%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1970s%3A%20The%20post-Apollo%20plans%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drawing%20of%20a%20slim%20spacecraft%20labeled%20e%20route%20spacecraft%20configuration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644f6517415a05fdd08957a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20artist's%20concept%20from%201969%20of%20a%20spacecraft%20for%20a%20crewed%20Mars%20mission.%3Cp%3EMarshall%20Space%20Flight%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20had%20just%20landed%20the%20first%20people%20on%20the%20moon%20in%201969%20as%20part%20of%20its%20Apollo%20Program%20and%20was%20ready%20for%20the%20next%20big%20step.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20a%20Richard%20Nixon-appointed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESpace%20Task%20Group%20issued%20a%20report%20that%20supported%20human%20flights%20to%20Mars%20in%201982.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20President%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENixon%20ignored%20most%20of%20the%201969%20report's%20suggestions%20in%20favor%20of%20what%20would%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchallenger-video-nasa-space-shuttle-program-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20Shuttle%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%20didn't%20involve%20going%20to%20Mars.%20It%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Apollo%20era%2C%20NASA%20didn't%20have%20to%20compete%20for%20funding%2C%20Shindell%20said.%20Now%2C%20Nixon's%20administration%20started%20cutting%20its%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20and%20many%20Americans%20wanted%20the%20government%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairandspace.si.edu%2Fstories%2Feditorial%2Fwhy-50-years-since-humans-went-moon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efocus%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20poverty%2C%20the%20environment%2C%20and%20other%20domestic%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20proponent%20of%20human%20Mars%20exploration%2C%20this%20is%20the%20problem%20you've%20faced%20ever%20since%20the%201970s%2C%26quot%3B%20Shindell%20said.%20Sending%20humans%20to%20the%20moon%20was%20already%20incredibly%20expensive%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20lot%20closer%20than%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1980s%3A%20Sally%20Ride's%20report%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222773%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sally%20ride%20women%20in%20space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F546e545f6bb3f7341edac8f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221990%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESally%20Ride%20communicates%20with%20ground%20controllers%20from%20the%20flight%20deck%20during%20the%20six-day%20mission%20in%20Challenger%2C%201983.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20National%20Archives%20and%20Records%20Administration%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201985%2C%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20appointed%20the%20National%20Commission%20on%20Space%20to%20envision%20the%20next%2050%20years%20of%20space%20travel%2C%20which%20involved%20the%20possibility%20of%20piloted%20vehicles%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20NASA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-challenger-space-shuttle-explosion-anniversary-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20Shuttle%20Challenger%3C%2Fa%3E%20exploded.%20The%20disaster%20affected%20how%20the%20agency%20thought%20about%20human%20space%20travel%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20there%20was%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20soul-searching%20within%20NASA%20about%20the%20use%20of%20expensive%20and%20risky%20human-rated%20launch%20vehicles%20like%20the%20shuttle%2C%26quot%3B%20William%20Sheehan%20and%20Jim%20Bell%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BDiscovering%20Mars%3A%20A%20History%20of%20Observation%20and%20Exploration%20of%20the%20Red%20Planet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20year%20later%2C%20though%2C%20NASA's%20administrator%20tasked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsally-ride-read-letter-nasa-become-first-american-woman-space-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronaut%20Sally%20Ride%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20laying%20out%20the%20agency's%20future%20space%20explorations.%20In%20her%20report%2C%20she%20explained%20what%20it%20would%20take%20for%20the%20US%20to%20land%20an%20astronaut%20on%20Mars%20by%202005.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20meet%20that%20timeline%2C%20NASA%20would%20need%20to%20triple%20its%20current%20budget%20in%20the%20next%20decade.%20That%20didn't%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1989%3A%2020%20years%20to%20Mars%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222258%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Five%20men%20in%20suits%20stand%20beneath%20NASA's%20Lunar%20Module%202%20at%20the%20National%20Air%20and%20Space%20Museum%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644f4c59fc063e829b15b71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwenty%20years%20after%20the%20Apollo%2011%20moon%20landing%2C%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%20announced%20the%20US%20would%20attempt%20to%20go%20to%20Mars.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Trippett%2FPool%20via%20CNP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201989%2C%20a%20crewed%20mission%20to%20Mars%20seemed%20back%20on%20the%20table%2C%20according%20to%20a%20speech%20by%20the%20newly%20elected%20President%20George%20H.W.%20Bush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhy%20Mars%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it%20is%20humanity's%20destiny%20to%20strive%2C%20to%20seek%2C%20to%20find.%20And%20because%20it%20is%20America's%20destiny%20to%20lead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA's%20response%20was%20the%20Space%20Exploration%20Initiative%2C%20an%20analysis%20of%20Bush's%20space%20exploration%20goals%2C%20which%20would%20cost%20an%20estimated%20%24400-%24500%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20Mars%20was%20still%20a%20long%20way%20off.%20The%20missions%20weren't%20expected%20to%20begin%20until%20after%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%3Cstrong%3E%