f%20the%20same%20name.%20Mr%20Watson%2C%20who%20regularly%20posts%20updates%20from%20his%20travels%20on%20Instagram%2C%20decided%20to%20try%20the%20fruit%20after%20learning%20that%20it%20was%20edible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20eat%20the%20cashew%20apple%20fruit%2C%20it's%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20bit%20bitter.%20I'd%20heard%20about%20it%20but%20never%20tried%20it%20in%20the%20flesh%2C%20so%20I%20bought%20it%2C%20went%20for%20a%20walk%20and%20started%20eating%20a%20few%20different%20fruits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20his%20first%20bite%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20I'd%20open%20it%20up%20-%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20passion%20fruit%2C%20and%20I%20bit%20into%20this%20sac%20which%20exploded%20straight%20away.%20Instantly%20it%20felt%20like%20fire%2C%20I%20could%20feel%20this%20fire%20going%20across%20my%20mouth.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20trouble%20began%20the%20next%20day%20when%20he%20woke%20up.%20His%20face%20was%20severely%20burnt%20and%20%26quot%3Bscabby%26quot%3B%2C%20seeming%20like%20it%20was%20doused%20with%20acid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20lips%20were%20all%20burnt%20they%20literally%20felt%20like%20they'd%20be%20dissolved%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20my%20lip%20had%20gone%20like%20baking%20paper%20for%20three%20or%20four%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled%2C%20adding%20that%20his%20hands%20were%20also%20discoloured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Watson%20later%20used%20Google%20search%20to%20understand%20the%20hazard.%20Notably%2C%20the%20caustic%20combination%20of%20cardol%20and%20anacardic%20acid%20found%20in%20cashew%20fruit%20can%20result%20in%20blisters%20when%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with%20the%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20the%2028-year-old%20did%20not%20go%20to%20the%20hospital%20because%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20pay%20a%20hefty%20medical%20bill.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20recovery%20process%20is%20still%20painful.%20%26quot%3BA%20couple%20of%20days%20ago%20I%20wa