eople%20moved%20in.%20Nearly%209%2C200%20people%20moved%20from%20Texas%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-florida-moving-to-missouri-pros-cons-insurance-boomer-taxes-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMissouri%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220cc2385b-f01e-4684-81df-b99d4ffa47f1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20Texas%2C%20moving%20to%20Missouri%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDonna%20moved%20around%20the%20northern%20US%20and%20Europe%20growing%20up%2C%20as%20her%20father%20was%20in%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20and%20her%20family%20eventually%20settled%20in%20the%20Dallas-Fort%20Worth%20area.%20After%20college%2C%20she%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20area%20and%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20paralegal%20before%20working%20for%20an%20information%20technology%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20formally%20stopped%20working%20after%20adopting%20her%20last%20kid%2C%20while%20her%20husband%20retired%20right%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20Though%20both%20lived%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-california-austin-texas-10-things-i-wish-i-knew-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20over%2040%20years%2C%20they%20knew%20Texas%20never%20felt%20like%20their%20permanent%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20son%20attended%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%2C%20where%20her%20husband%20went%2C%20and%20he%20settled%20in%20St.%20Louis.%20Donna%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20state%20for%20their%20retirement%2C%20as%20she%20knew%20she%20couldn't%20stand%20another%20Texas%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20got%20situated%20in%20Texas%2C%20I%20just%20didn't%20feel%20like%20I%20fit%20in.%20I%20wasn't%20a%20Southerner.%20I%20wasn't%20a%20Texan%2C%26quot%3B%20Donna%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20surprises%20me%20everybody's%20moving%20to%20Texas.%20I'm%20like%2C%20you%20know%20how%20hot%20it%20is%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20moved%20to%20Missouri%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20their%20son%20and%20escape%20the%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20want%20to%20just%20be%20the%20parents%20that%20lived%20somewhere%20else%20and%20came%20in%20on%20a%20plane%20to%20visit%20you%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20and%20then%20they%20were%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20Donna%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20actually%20be%20close%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20looked%20around%20St.%20Louis%20for%20two%20years%20but%20couldn't%20find%20much%20on%20the%20market.%20They%20would%20fly%20in%2C%20tour%20five%20homes%2C%20and%20nearly%20all%20would%20be%20bought%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day.%20She%20said%20the%20ones%20that%20weren't%20selling%20fast%20would%20be%20built%20on%20hills%20or%20back%20up%20onto%20a%20highway.%20Finally%2C%20she%20got%20the%20call%20for%20a%20new%20home%20on%20the%20market.%20She%20flew%20in%20on%20a%20Friday%20morning%20in%20January%202020%20by%20herself%2C%20and%20by%20that%20night%2C%20they%20signed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20home%20was%20bigger%20and%20more%20expensive%20than%20what%20they%20originally%20wanted%2C%20though%20they%20were%20grateful%20to%20find%20something%20that%20worked.%20They%20loved%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20and%20they%20envisioned%20they%20would%20renovate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-california-missouri-bought-house-sight-unseen-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMissouri%3C%2Fa%3E%20home%20while%20working%20on%20selling%20the%20Texas%20home.%20The%20process%20took%20longer%20than%20they%20expected%2C%20though%20they%20eventually%20got%20a%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a788c97-d64b-4730-8918-9dfa406eadc6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearning%20the%20hard%20way%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDonna%20said%20she%20immediately%20felt%20like%20she%20was%20missing%20home%20once%20she%20moved%20in%20September%202020.%20Still%2C%20she%20was%20optimistic%20about%20life%20in%20Missouri%2C%20as%20she%20figured%20it%20was%20quieter%20and%20slower-paced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20new%20neighborhood%20was%20similar%20to%20Dallas%2C%20though%20she%20said%20it's%20more%20spread%20out.%20It's%20taken%20some%20time%20to%20get%20used%20to%20driving%20everywhere%2C%20which%20she%20said%20has%20been%20burdensome%20as%20they%20age.%20Still%2C%20she%20values%20having%20many%20hills%20and%20trees%2C%20unlike%20in%20Texas%2C%20where%20her%20community%20was%20more%20flat%20and%20monotonous.%20Her%20new%20neighborhood%20is%20also%20more%20family-oriented%20and%20diverse%2C%20though%20she%20said%20her%20neighbors%20were%20confused%20about%20why%20she%20would%20move%20from%20Dallas%2C%20which%20they%20perceive%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20sexy%20place%20to%20live.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20in%20St.%20Louis%20are%20so%20friendly%20and%20so%20helpful%2C%26quot%3B%20Donna%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20many%20of%20those%20she%20knew%20in%20Texas%20were%20friendly%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20surface%26quot%3B%20and%20didn't%20often%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20say%20hello.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20into%2C%20say%2C%20a%20Lowe's%2C%20and%20you%20need%20help%2C%20oh%20my%20gosh%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20help.%20People%20here%20are%20hardworking%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20complain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20that%20she%20should%20have%20researched%20some%20of%20the%20hidden%20costs%2C%20Donna%20said%20everything%20was%20unexpectedly%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20she%20thought.%20She%20noticed%20first%20that%20gas%20was%20more%20expensive%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-cost-of-living-nyc-kansas-city-midwest-rent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMissouri%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20though%20Texas%20and%20Missouri%2C%20on%20average%2C%20are%20now%20about%20the%20same%20per%20gallon%20nationally%2C%20she%20said%20her%20area%20is%20about%2075%20cents%20more%20expensive%20per%20ga