0and%20central%20India.%20On%20Sunday%2C%20temperatures%20soared%20to%20an%20unprecedented%2050%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20Rajasthan's%20Phalodi.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20temperature%20recorded%20in%20India%20since%20June%202019%2C%20when%20Churu%2C%20another%20city%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20hit%2050.8%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EExtreme%20Heat%20Across%20North%20India%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20heatwave%20is%20not%20just%20confined%20to%20the%20northern%20plains%20but%20has%20also%20impacted%20the%20hills%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Assam%2C%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20During%20the%20sixth%20phase%20of%20the%20ongoing%20general%20elections%2C%20voters%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Delhi%20faced%20extreme%20heat%2C%20with%20temperatures%20in%20the%20capital%20exceeding%2045%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20several%20locations.%20Polling%20booths%20in%20many%20areas%20lacked%20adequate%20facilities%20like%20water%2C%20coolers%2C%20and%20chairs%2C%20leading%20to%20voters%20fainting%20due%20to%20the%20harsh%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fpdpp0c9o_delhi-heatwave-_625x300_27_May_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Reuters%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20cities%20across%20India%20reported%20record-breaking%20temperatures%20recently.%20In%20West%20Bengal's%20Cooch%20Behar%2C%20the%20temperature%20reached%2040.5%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20while%20Assam's%20Silchar%20hit%2040%20degrees%2C%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh's%20Itanagar%20recorded%2040.5%20degrees%20Celsius.%20These%20extreme%20temperatures%20have%20been%20widespread%2C%20with%20at%20least%2017%20locations%20in%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20recording%20temperatures%20of%2045%20degrees%20Celsius%20or%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajasthan%20has%20been%20particularly%20affected%2C%20with%20Barmer%20reaching%2048.8%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20Jaisalmer%2048%20degrees%2C%20and%20Bikaner%2047.2%20degrees.%20The%20state's%20disaster%20management%20department%20has%20directed%20district%20collectors%20to%20provide%20necessary%20relief%20to%20people%2C%20animals%2C%20and%20birds.%20The%20extreme%20heat%20is%20expected%20to%20persist%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20Maharashtra%20until%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20with%20severe%20conditions%20also%20affecting%20the%20hills%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Assam%2C%20and%20Meghalaya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F7t85u3q8_delhi-heatwave-_625x300_27_May_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20ANI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%20and%20Punjab%20are%20also%20under%20severe%20heatwave%20conditions%2C%20with%20temperatures%20soaring%20above%20normal%20limits.%20In%20Haryana%2C%20Mahendragarh%20recorded%2047%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20while%20Rohtak%20and%20Hisar%20reported%2046.7%20and%2046%20degrees%2C%20respectively.%20Similarly%2C%20Punjab's%20Amritsar%20reached%2045.2%20degrees%2C%20and%20Ludhiana%2044.8%20degrees.%20Chandigarh%2C%20the%20common%20capital%20of%20both%20states%2C%20saw%20temperatures%20of%2044.5%20degrees%20Celsius.%20The%20heatwave%20is%20expected%20to%20continue%20in%20these%20regions%20until%20May%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMD%20has%20issued%20a%20'red'%20warning%20for%20several%20regions%2C%20including%20Rajasthan%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Delhi%2C%20west%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Gujarat.%20This%20indicates%20a%20very%20high%20likelihood%20of%20heat%20illness%20and%20heatstroke%20across%20all%20age%20groups.%20The%20IMD%20also%20noted%20that%20warm%20night%20conditions%20will%20exacerbate%20heat%20stress%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Delhi%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%20over%20the%20next%20four%20days.%20High%20night%20temperatures%20are%20especially%20dangerous%20as%20they%20prevent%20the%20body%20from%20cooling%20down%2C%20an%20issue%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20urban%20heat%20island%20effect%2C%20where%20cities%20remain%20significantly%20hotter%20than%20their%20rural%20surroundings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeat%20Multiplier%20Effect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkash%20Vashishtha%2C%20founder-secretary%20of%20the%20Society%20for%20Protection%20of%20Environment%20and%20Biodiversity%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20news%20agency%20PTI%2C%20explained%20that%20urban%20areas%20like%20Delhi-NCR%20become%20heat%20chambers%20due%20to%20land%20and%20surface%20concretisation%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20heat%20multiplier%20effect.%20The%20urban%20heat%20island%20effect%20traps%20heat%20in%20the%20lower%20atmosphere%2C%20significantly%20raising%20ambient%20temperatures.%20To%20mitigate%20this%2C%20Mr%20Vashishtha%20said%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20keep%20ground%20surfaces%20vegetated%20to%20absorb%20solar%20radiation%20and%20reduce%20heat%20reflection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intense%20heat%20in%20India%20is%20also%20straining%20power%20grids%20and%20depleting%20water%20bodies%2C%20triggering%20drought-like%20conditions%20in%20various%20regions.%20The%20Central%20Water%20Commission%20reported%20that%20water%20storage%20in%20150%20major%20reservoirs%20reached%20a%20five-year%20low%20last%20week%2C%20worsening%20water%20shortages%20and%20affecting%20hydropower%20generation.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20water%20levels%20in%20the%20Yamuna%20river%20have%20dropped%2C%20impacting%20water%20supply.%20The%20city's%20power%20demand%20hit%20a%20record%208%2C000%20megawatts%20as%20air%20conditioners%20and%20coolers%20ran%20at%20full%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heatwave%20is%20placing%20a%20significant%20burden%20on%20low-income%20households%2C%20which%20often%20have%20limited%20access%20to%20water%20and%20cooling%20facilities.%20Poorly%20ventilated%20and%20inadequately%20sheltered%20informal%20housing%20exacerbates%20the%20impact%20of%20extreme%20heat%20on%20vulnerable%20populations.%20Outdoor%20workers%2C%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20children%20are%20at%20higher%20risk%20of%20heat%20exhaustion%20and%20heatstroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnna%20Walnycki%20of%20the%20London-based%20International%20Institute%20for%20Environment%20and%20Development%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLow-income%20households%20have%20limited%20capacity%20to%20adapt%20to%20extreme%20heat%20because%20of%20poor%20access%20to%20water%20and%20electricity.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20design%20and%20construction%20of%20informal%20houses%20often%20mean%20there%20is%20poor%20ventilation%20and%20little%20shelter%20from%20extreme%20heat.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fm0atasvg_delhi-heatwave-_625x300_27_May_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Reuters%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20reports%20that%20over%20166%2C000%20people%20died%20from%20heatwaves%20between%201998%20and%202017%2C%20with%20India%20alone%20reporting%203%2C812%20deaths%20due%20to%20heatwaves%20between%202015%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeatwaves%20also%20reduce%20productivity%20and%20affect%20learning%20outcomes%20for%20children.%20Studies%20show%20that%20students%20perform%20worse%20during%20hot%20school%20years%2C%20and%20with%2015%25%20of%20government%20schools%20lacking%20functional%20electricity%2C%20rural%20education%20is%20disproportionately%20affected.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20adequate%20cold-chain%20infrastructure%20causes%20significant%20damage%20to%20fresh%20produce%2C%20leading%20to%20food%20losses%20worth%20%2413%20billion%20annually%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20World%20Bank%20report%2C%20India%20could%20account%20for%2034%20million%20of%20the%20projected%2080%20million%20global%20job%20losses%20from%20heat%20stress-associated%20productivity%20decline%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20summary%2C%20the%20severe%20heatwave%20conditions%20in%20Delhi%20and%20surrounding%20regions%20are%20a%20result%20of%20a%20combination%20of%20urban%20heat%20island%20effects%20and%20broader%20climatic%20patterns%20affecting%20northern%20and%20central%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EIndia.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E(With%20inputs%20from%20PTI)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716795420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F002u08u_delhi-heatwave-_625x300_27_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-heatwave-delhi-weather-explained-why-is-it-so-hot-in-delhi-and-what-you-should-do-to-stay-safe-5755086%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20is%20currently%20experiencing%20an%20intense%20heatwave%2C%20with%20temperatures%20forecasted%20to%20reach%20a%20staggering%2046%20degrees%20Celsius.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-heatwave-delhi-weather-explained-why-is-it-so-hot-in-delhi-and-what-you-should-do-to-stay-safe-5755086%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-heatwave-delhi-weather-explained-why-is-it-so-hot-in-delhi-and-what-you-should-do-to-stay-safe-5755086